title: Taylor Swift, 29, shares photo from when she was 16 as she thanks fans
text:
Taylor Swift took a trip down memory lane on Thursday afternoon.

The Lover singer posted a flashback photo from when she was only 16-years-old and performing for a small group of people. The Pennsylvania native said at the time she only hoped that her success would continue.

Next, the 29-year-old Grammy winner shared another photo of a recent sold-out concert.

Teen spirit: Taylor Swift took a trip down memory lane on Thursday afternoon. The Lover singer posted a flashback photo from when she was only 16-years-old and performing for a small group of people by a lake

Ambition: Swift's caption was long and heartfelt. 'I said in an interview 13 years ago "I'm just hoping that I have a second album that does as well as the first and someday get to be a headliner, and always be the same person that I started out as"'

Swift's caption was long and heartfelt.

'I said in an interview 13 years ago "I'm just hoping that I have a second album that does as well as the first and someday get to be a headliner, and always be the same person that I started out as.”

'Scrolling through your posts today has me feeling all the feelings & I want to thank you.

'Because of you, there was a 2nd 3rd 4th 5th 6th and 7th album.'

You've come a long way baby: Next, the 29-year-old Grammy winner shared another photo of a recent sold-out concert

She then went on to say they all made it happen.

'You guys made me into a headliner because you wanted to see me play. And your support all these years is what’s helped me stay true to that kid I was when I started out. '

Her hashtag was for '13 years of taylor swift.'

She so far has sold 50M albums and is one of the best-selling music artists of all time.

Superstar: There were no bigger star at We Can Survive than the music festival's headliner, Swift, who took the stage at the Hollywood Bowl late on Saturday night

The blonde star got her start in 2006 with her debut album and her second album Fearless came out in 2008.

Next came 2010's Speak Now then 2012's Red. Her fifth album was 1989, which came out in 2014.

In 2017 came her sixth album, Reputation. This year her seventh album is Lover.

This comes days after the Red singer sold out Radio.com's seventh annual We Can Survive music festival at the Hollywood Bowl late on Saturday night.

The 29-year-old Shake It Off hitmaker dazzled in a black sequined romper for her energetic performance.
description: The Lover singer posted a flashback photo from when she was only 16-years-old and performing. The Pennsylvania native said at the time she only hoped that her success would continue.
